cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper analyzes the role of popularity and novelty in attracting user attention to dynamic websites, which falls under the sub-categories of social media analysis (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), cybernetics (cs.CY), and sound and music computing (cs.SD). The paper discusses strategies for maximizing attention, which is relevant to these sub-categories.
